When it comes to analyzing the neonatal hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy market, it is crucial to break down the market into various segments to understand the dynamics of each component. The market can be segmented based on diagnosis and treatment options. Under the diagnosis segment, key methods such as MRI, CT, and EEG play a significant role in identifying the condition in neonates. These diagnostic tools aid healthcare professionals in assessing the extent of brain damage and planning appropriate interventions. On the treatment front, segments include therapeutic hypothermia, medication options, and in severe cases, surgical interventions. Therapeutic hypothermia has emerged as a standard treatment for neonatal HIE, showcasing promising outcomes in reducing long-term neurological deficits.

